{"key":"post-10788027","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10788027</id>\n<content>Interesting.&amp;nbsp; I use the autoclavable filter patch bags from Unicorn Bag Company and have never had a single bag melt from contacting the sides of the PC.&amp;nbsp; Obviously you have to elevate them off the bottom because that's where the heat is applied, but the sides shouldn't be hot enough to melt them.&amp;nbsp; The important thing is to get spacers in place to hold the bags away from the edges so steam can completely surround them.&amp;nbsp; If not, your substrate may not be fully sterilized.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10788044</next>\n<prev>10787816</prev>\n<first>10787425</first>\n<last>10794752</last>\n<when>1249264283</when>\n<utime>08/03/09 04:51 AM</utime>\n</post>"}